@ontos 1.0
@title App design example
@type app-design
@updated 2026-06-05

- Workspace design @id(workspace-design) #app #design
  status: active
  owner: product
  purpose: Define the structure for a project context workspace.
  current:
    - Navigation, node details, and export actions are in scope.
    - Marketing pages are out of scope for this document.
  ai_task: Suggest interaction improvements without changing public naming.
  ai_boundary: Do not rename protocol, CLI, npm scope, or package names.
  risk:
    - Users may confuse document structure with a task tracker.
  verify:
    - Validate the example with ontosfmt.
    - Export to HTML and inspect heading hierarchy.
  history:
    - 2026-06-05 created as official app design example.

  - Navigation model @id(navigation-model) #ux
    status: planned
    depends_on: [[workspace-design]]
    acceptance:
      - Node tree supports keyboard focus.
      - Current node path remains visible.

    - Node tree states @id(node-tree-states) #interaction
      purpose: Capture expanded, collapsed, focused, and search states.
      verify:
        - Search result count is visible.
        - Focused node can be copied as text.
